6. Difference between MVC and MVVM?
| MVC                      | MVVM                     |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------ |
| Controller handles input | ViewModel handles state  |
| View is passive          | View is data-bound       |
| Less suited for SPA      | Ideal for SPA frameworks |

7. What is MVC in REST APIs?
    Controller handles HTTPS endpoints
    Model handles the buisness logic
    View usually json/xml instead of html

8. How does MVC improve testability?
    Models can be tested independenly
    Controller can be used mock modela
    Views are simple and require minimal testing

9. Where should validation logic go?
    Validation should be placed in the Model or Service layer, not in the View.
